00:13:33,778 --> 00:13:36,246
of his own death.

258
00:13:36,314 --> 00:13:37,915
According to
one account,

259
00:13:37,982 --> 00:13:40,884
it is in the early
morning hours of April 2nd

260
00:13:40,952 --> 00:13:44,320
and Lincoln is aboard the
steamship River Queen.

261
00:13:44,387 --> 00:13:46,355
He has left Washington
to visit the warfront

262
00:13:46,423 --> 00:13:48,557
where General
Ulysses S. Grant

263
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:51,192
is poised to capture
the Confederate capital

264
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:54,128
of Richmond, Virginia.

265
00:13:54,196 --> 00:13:57,298
<i>[cannon fire]</i>

266
00:13:57,366 --> 00:14:01,268
Abraham Lincoln has
13 days to live.

267
00:14:02,971 --> 00:14:07,874
<i>[female singing]</i>

268
00:14:08,776 --> 00:14:10,943
Tom Hanks: On
April 3nd, 1865,

269
00:14:11,011 --> 00:14:13,813
Confederate forces set
fire to their own capital

270
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:16,415
of Richmond, Virginia
before evacuating ahead of

271
00:14:16,483 --> 00:14:20,118
advancing Union troops.

272
00:14:20,186 --> 00:14:21,653
Confederate president
Jefferson Davis

273
00:14:21,721 --> 00:14:23,421
escapes by train.

274
00:14:23,489 --> 00:14:26,992
Abandons his White
House of the Confederacy.

275
00:14:27,059 --> 00:14:29,427
And Abraham Lincoln
lands in Richmond to

276
00:14:29,495 --> 00:14:34,565
view the devastated ruins
of this American city.

277
00:14:37,836 --> 00:14:41,072
Soldier: Form up!

278
00:14:48,380 --> 00:14:50,147
Abraham Lincoln: Do
any of you know the

279
00:14:50,215 --> 00:14:52,549
way to General
Weitzel's headquarters?

280
00:14:52,617 --> 00:14:54,517
Freed Slave:
Yas-suh, Master Lincoln.

281
00:14:54,585 --> 00:14:55,785
I know the way!

282
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:59,522
Admiral Porter:
Fix bayonets!

283
00:15:05,762 --> 00:15:09,531
<i>[train whistles].</i>

284
00:15:09,599 --> 00:15:10,932
Abraham Lincoln: Look.

285
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,000
<i>[whistle].</i>

286
00:15:13,067 --> 00:15:16,269
Crook: Window.

287
00:15:20,308 --> 00:15:21,875
Abraham Lincoln:
Thank God I have

288
00:15:21,943 --> 00:15:25,179
lived to see
this day.

289
00:15:25,246 --> 00:15:27,982
On we go.

290
00:15:33,322 --> 00:15:36,658
Tad Lincoln: Papa-day.

291
00:15:39,361 --> 00:15:41,663
Old Slave: May de
good Lord bless and

292
00:15:41,730 --> 00:15:46,334
keep you safe,
Massa Lincoln.

293
00:15:50,605 --> 00:15:52,772
Abraham Lincoln:
You are a free citizen

294
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,474
of this republic.

295
00:15:54,542 --> 00:15:56,075
Kneel to God only.

296
00:15:56,143 --> 00:16:01,549
And thank him for the
liberty that is yours.

297
00:16:05,254 --> 00:16:07,122
Tom Hanks: It's one of
the most unforgettable

298
00:16:07,190 --> 00:16:09,358
scenes in
American history.

299
00:16:09,426 --> 00:16:12,027
An American President
walking the streets of a

300
00:16:12,095 --> 00:16:16,932
fallen rebel capital in
the midst of a Civil War.

301
00:16:20,337 --> 00:16:22,905
Scarcely 36 hours
after Jefferson Davis

302
00:16:22,973 --> 00:16:24,973
has fled his capital,

303
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:26,642
Abraham Lincoln
arrives at the

304
00:16:26,709 --> 00:16:31,045
surrendered home of the
Confederate president.

305
00:16:31,313 --> 00:16:32,981
Crook: I am informed
that General Weitzel

