00:16:33,048 --> 00:16:35,116
is on his way, sir.

307
00:16:35,184 --> 00:16:39,721
And this is Mrs. O'Melia,
the housekeeper.

308
00:16:40,122 --> 00:16:43,091
Abraham Lincoln: Ma'am,
might you direct me to

309
00:16:43,159 --> 00:16:47,496
President Davis' desk?

310
00:16:57,239 --> 00:17:02,978
So this must have been
President Davis' chair.

311
00:17:18,061 --> 00:17:19,661
Tom Hanks:
Jefferson Davis will soon

312
00:17:19,729 --> 00:17:22,263
be captured in Georgia.

313
00:17:22,331 --> 00:17:24,098
He will die 24
years later,

314
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:26,567
at the age of 81.

315
00:17:26,635 --> 00:17:29,971
Abraham Lincoln:
This is whence

316
00:17:30,039 --> 00:17:38,014
Mr. Jefferson Davis has
conducted his war, Tad.

317
00:17:39,884 --> 00:17:41,851
Tom Hanks: But
Abraham Lincoln has

318
00:17:41,919 --> 00:17:46,257
less than 11
days to live.

319
00:17:46,892 --> 00:17:50,861
Abraham Lincoln: Might I
have a glass of water?

320
00:17:51,096 --> 00:17:52,530
Tom Hanks: Ironically,
on this day,

321
00:17:52,598 --> 00:17:55,466
Tad's 12th birthday,
April 4th, 1865,

